---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
    title="About Us - JSON Utility Kit"
    description="Discover the core mission and values behind JSON Utility Kit. A secure browser-based toolset designed to give developers total privacy."
>
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="text-center max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-12">
            <h1
                class="text-3xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-gray-900 dark:text-white sm:text-4xl"
            >
                About JSON Utility Kit
            </h1>
            <p class="mt-3 text-lg text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
                Total data privacy, optimal performance, and effortless data
                handling.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div
            class="prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-6 leading-relaxed"
        >
            <p>
                <strong>JSON Utility Kit</strong> was built for a simple reason: developers
                and data administrators need high-quality JSON tools every single
                day, but pasting sensitive configs, customer details, or production
                payloads into random online text boxes poses a massive security vulnerability.
            </p>

            <h2
                class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4"
            >
                Our Core Mission: 100% Secure Local Execution
            </h2>
            <p>
                Almost every other "JSON formatter" on the market streams your
                pasted data to their servers for background formatting, or logs
                your IP with database histories.
            </p>
            <p>
                <strong>JSON Utility Kit is entirely serverless.</strong> Every tool—from
                the validator to the CSV-to-JSON parser—runs natively inside your
                browser using client-side JavaScript. This means your data is never
                uploaded, never intercepted, and never saved. You can even load our
                webpage, disconnect your computer from the Wi-Fi completely, and continue
                using the tools offline.
            </p>

            <h2
                class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4"
            >
                Who Is This Built For?
            </h2>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                <li>
                    <strong>Software Engineers:</strong> Debugging REST or GraphQL
                    API response payloads.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Data Scientists & Analysts:</strong> Transitioning data
                    arrays from nested JSON to tabular CSV formats.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>QA Engineers:</strong> Checking syntax against standard
                    JSON limits to prevent integration crashes.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>DevOps Architects:</strong> Checking server variables
                    and sorting configuration files before deployment.
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h2
                class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4"
            >
                Features Included
            </h2>
            <p>
                Our first version delivers essential JSON tools optimized for
                modern screens, responsive sizes, and high rendering speeds:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                <li>
                    <strong>JSON Formatter & Beautifier:</strong> Instant prettifying
                    with customized indentation.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>JSON Validator:</strong> Precise syntax analysis with
                    detailed exception spots.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>JSON Viewer:</strong> Expandable and interactive tree
                    renderer with property-path copying.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>JSON Minifier:</strong> High-ratio lossless compression
                    to reduce transfer overhead.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>JSON Editor:</strong> Sort keys, adjust syntax, and review
                    layouts simultaneously.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>JSON to CSV & CSV to JSON:</strong> Move structured lists
                    between spreadsheets and code seamlessly.
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</Layout>
